<HEAD>

<TITLE>REGULATION XIV - TOXICS AND OTHER NON-CRITERIA POLLUTANTS </TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="HTM Assistant PRO">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Jane Powers">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><CENTER>REGULATION XIV </H1>

<H2>TOXICS AND OTHER NON-CRITERIA POLLUTANTS </CENTER></H2>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1401.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1401.html">Rule 1401 </A> - <B>New Source Review of Carcinogenic Air Contaminants</B> <I>(Amended December 7, 1990)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1402.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1402.html">Rule 1402 </A> - <B>Control of Toxic Air Contaminants from Existing Sources</B> <I>(Adopted April 8, 1994)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1403.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1403.html">Rule 1403 </A> - <B>Asbestos Emissions from Demolition/Renovation Activities</B> <I>(Amended April 8, 1994)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1404.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1404.html">Rule 1404 </A> - <B>Hexavalent Chromium Emissions from Cooling Towers</B><I> (Amended April 6, 1990)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1405.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1405.html">Rule 1405 </A> - <B>Control of  Ethylene Oxide and Chlorofluorocarbon Emissions from Sterilization or Fumigation Processes</B> <I>(Amended January 4, 1991)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1406.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1406.html">Rule 1406 </A> - <B>Control of Dioxin Emissions from Medical Waste Incinerators
</B><I> (Amended July 8, 1994)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1407.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1407.html">Rule 1407 </A> - <B>Control of Emissions of Arsenic, Cadmium, and Nickel from Non-Ferrous Metal Melting Operations</B> <I>(Adopted July 8, 1994)</I>

<LI><A HREF="/rules/doc/r1410.doc"><IMG SRC="/icon/word.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="r1410.html">Rule 1410 </A> - <B>Hydrogen Fluoride Storage and Use</B> <I>(Suspended June 8, 1992)</I>

