<HEAD>

<TITLE>REGULATION XXXI - ACID RAIN PERMIT PROGRAM </TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="HTML Assistant ">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Ernest Pang">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><CENTER>REGULATION <A HREF="#reg31">XXXI</A> </H1>

<H2>ACID RAIN PERMIT PROGRAM</CENTER> </H2>
<CENTER><I>(Adopted February 10, 1995)</I></CENTER>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#a">Subpart A </A> - <B>Acid Rain Program General Provisions</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#b">Subpart B </A> - <B>Designated Representative</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#c">Subpart C </A> - <B>Acid Rain Applications</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#d">Subpart D </A> - <B>Acid Rain Compliance Plan and Compliance Options</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#e">Subpart E </A> - <B>Acid Rain Permit Contents</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#g">Subpart G </A> - <B>Acid Rain Phase II Implementation</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#h">Subpart H </A> - <B>Permit Revisions</B><P>
<LI><A HREF="#i">Subpart I </A> - <B>Compliance Certification </B><P>
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
<A NAME="reg31"></A>(Adopted February 10, 1995)
<H3>REGULATION XXXI. ACID RAIN PERMIT PROGRAM </H3>

<P>
The provisions of Part 72, Chapter I, Title 40, of the Code of Federal Regulations (CFR) applicable to the subparts listed in this Regulation were adopted by the South Coast Air Quality Management District on the date shown and were made part of the Rules and Regulations of the South Coast Air Quality Management District.
<P>
The provisions of this Regulation apply to the owner or operator of any stationary source for which an acid rain permit is required under this Regulation. For the purpose of this Regulation, the words &quot;permitting authority&quot; as used in Part 72, Chapter I, Title 40, of the CFR shall mean the Executive Officer or designee of the South Coast Air Quality Management District and the word &quot;Administrator&quot; shall mean the Administrator of the United States Environmental Protection Agency.
<P>
<U><B>Part 72</B></U> 
<H3><A NAME="a"></A>SUBPART A &nbsp; - &nbsp; ACID RAIN PROGRAM GENERAL PROVISIONS
</H3>

<P>
(58FR3590, January 11, 1993) (Adopted Feb. 10, 1995)
<P>
(58FR15634, March 23, 1993) (Adopted Feb. 10, 1995) 

<H3><A NAME="b"></A>SUBPART B &nbsp; - &nbsp; DESIGNATED REPRESENTATIVE </H3>

<P>
(58FR3590, January 11, 1993) (Adopted Feb. 10, 1995) 

<H3><A NAME="c"></A>SUBPART C &nbsp; - &nbsp; ACID RAIN APPLICATIONS </H3>

