<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>RULE 309 - Fees for Regulation XVI Plans</TITLE>
<LINK REL="ToC" HREF="httoc.htm">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Ernest Pang">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P> (Adopted June 10, 1994)(Amended May 10, 1996)

<P><B>RULE 309. FEES FOR REGULATION XVI PLANS</B>

<P><B>(a) Applicability</B>
<BR> Provisions of this rule shall apply to fees assessed for plans required by Regulation XVI.  Fees shall be paid for:
<OL>
<LI> Rule 1610 Scrapping Plans

<P><LI> Regulation XVI MSERC Applications and Compliance Plans
</OL>

<P><B>(b) Definitions</B>
<BR> For the purpose of this rule the following definitions shall apply:
<OL>
<LI>PLAN is any data and/or test report required by federal or state law, or District rules and regulations to be submitted to the District.  Plans include, but are not limited to, the following:  Rule 1610 Scrapping Plans, Regulation XVI MSERC Applications, and Regulation XVI Compliance Plans.
<P><LI> SMALL BUSINESS is as defined in Rule 102.
</OL>

<P><B>(c) Plan Filing and Evaluation Fee</B>
<OL>
<LI>Rule 1610 Scrapping Plans shall be assessed a $ 1,012.00 filing and evaluation fee.  The fee shall be paid at the time of plan submittal.
<P><LI>Regulation XVI Compliance Plans shall be assessed a filing fee of $76.80 and an evaluation fee of $256.00 at the time of submittal.
<P><LI>Regulation XVI MSERC Applications shall be assessed a filing fee of $76.80 and an evaluation fee of $256.00 at the time of submittal.
<P><LI>Additional evaluation fees shall be assessed at the rate of $76.81 per person per hour if necessary.
<P><LI>For small businesses filing scrapping plans, MSERC applications, and compliance plans, the fees assessed shall be fifty percent (50%) of the amounts specified in paragraphs (c)(1), (c)(2), (c)(3), and (c)(4).
</OL>

<P><B>(d) Refunds</B>
<OL>
<LI>If a scrapping plan, MSERC application, or a compliance plan is canceled, plan filing and evaluation fees, less the plan cancellation fee, will be refunded:
<P>
<UL> (A) If it is determined that the plan was not required pursuant to District rules; or
<P> (B) The plan evaluation procedure has not been initiated by District staff.
</UL>
<P><LI>The plan cancellation fee will be $102.40.
<P><LI>Claims for refund of any fee required by this rule shall be submitted in writing within one (1) year after the fee was paid.
<P><LI>The cancellation fee shall not apply when the plan was filed based on an erroneous District request.
</OL>

<P><B>(e) Government Agencies</B>
<BR> Federal, state, or local government agencies or public districts shall pay all fees.
<P><BR>

</BODY></HTML>
<P>

</DOC>
