<TITLE>Business Assistance Services</TITLE>
<meta name = "OPERATOR" content = "Lana Bowman">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50 SRC="/icon/bassist.gif" ><CLEAR=LEFT>
<CENTER>
<H2>Business Assistance</H2>
<IMG SRC="/icon/line4.gif"></CENTER>

<h3>Business Assistance Services</h3>
<P>The AQMD offers the following services to businesses.  For more information contact:</P>
<p><a id = "bc" name = "bc"><B>Billing and Customer Service</B>
<br>This section responds to billing inquiries from permit holders and applicants; researches historical facility records to resolve problems associated with fees billed; and mails out invoices, including annual operating fee invoices.  
<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:mcruz@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (mcruz@aqmd.gov) or by phone (909) 396-2900.
<P><a id = "cc" name = "cc"><B>Compliance Course Information</B>
<br>Compliance promotion classes feature experienced field inspectors who help facility owners and operators learn about compliance with AQMD source specific rule requirements.  Classes also provide information about enforcement actions, variances and Hearing Board, and other compliance resources available through the AQMD.
<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:compliance-classes@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (compliance-classes@aqmd.gov) or by phone (800-4-CLN-AIR) (800-425-6247).
<P><a id = "ec" name = "ec"><B>Office of Economic Development and Business Retention</B>
<br>Do you want to expand or relocate you business?  Do you want or need air quality rules explained to you?  Do you need technical assistance to help you observe emission limits?  The office will prioritize and expedite permits, and help you navigate through the permit process.  If you have technical problems, or require a permit variance, the office can act as an advocate on your behalf. The office has identified cleaner products and processes and developed new regulatory approaches.
<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:watkinsl@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (watkinsl@aqmd.gov) or phone (909) 396-3246.
<P><a id = "fc" name = "fc"><B>Fee Review Committee</B>
<br>This committee resolves permit fee disputes between regulated firms and the AQMD.  The committee can also under certain circumstances provide additional time for payment of fees.
<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:lnolken@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (lnolker@aqmd.gov) or by phone: (909) 396-2744.
<P><a id = "gc" name = "gc"><B>Permit Application Information</B>
<br>Permit Services provides permit application forms, reviews applications to determine administrative completeness, verifies fee filing amounts, and resolves technical questions from applications  permit application filing procedures.  Staff also prescreens new applications to validate equipment or facility type and filing fee amounts prior to final disposition of a permit application package.  If you are installing standard off-the-shelf types of equipment or pre-certified equipment, ask if your application qualifies for simpler and less expensive registration.
<br>(Contact by <A HREF="mailto:permit_svcs@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (permit_svcs@aqmd.gov) or by phone: (909) 396-2468. 
<P><a id = "hc" name = "hc"><B>Public Advisor&#146;s Office</B>
<br>As the primary liaison with all segments of the public, including, local government, schools and businesses, the Public Advisor provides access to the rule and policy development process of the AQMD.   The Public Advisor also operates the AQMD&#146;s Public Information Center which offers 24-hour access to obtain copies of rules and regulations, other AQMD documents and air quality information.<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:lbowen@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A>: (lbowen@aqmd.gov) or by phone: (909) 396-3235.
<P><a id = "ic" name = "ic"></a><a href = "basb.html"><B>Small Business Assistance Office </B></a>
<br>The Small Business Assistance staff helps small business owners communicate with AQMD. It helps owners find out which rules apply to their operations, fill out applications for permits and variances, and find the most cost-effective ways to comply with rules. The group provides walk-up assistance and on-site technical and compliance assistance by appointment.  The office also helps small businesses obtain financing to purchase air quality pollution control equipment.<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:llockie@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (llockie@aqmd.gov) or by phone: (800) 388-2121.
<P></a><B>Transportation (Rule 2202) Assistance</B><a id = "ta" name = "ta"><br>The new AQMD Technical Assistance Team assists employers in learning about which options available under Rule 2202 (On-Road Motor Vehicle Mitigation Options) are the most cost effective and practical.  Members of the Technical Assistance Team are available by appointment to meet with employers and speak to groups about how they can save money while helping to clean the air.
<br>Contact by <A HREF="mailto:vloveland@aqmd.gov">E-Mail</A> (vloveland@aqmd.gov) or by phone: (909) 396-3063.  
<BR><CENTER><IMG SRC="/icon/line4.gif"></CENTER>
