<HEAD>
<TITLE>RULE 203. Permit to Operate</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
 (Adopted January 9, 1976)(Amended January 5, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 203. PERMIT TO OPERATE</B>
<P>
(a) A person shall not operate or use any equipment, the use of
which may cause the issuance of air contaminants, or the use of
which may reduce or control the issuance of air contaminants,
without first obtaining a written permit to operate from the Executive
Officer or except as provided in Rule 202.  
<P>
(b)<TT> </TT>The equipment shall not be operated contrary to the
conditions specified in the permit to operate.
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

