<HEAD>
<TITLE>RULE 205 - Expiration of Permits to Construct</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
 (Adopted January 9, 1976)(Amended January 5, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 205. EXPIRATION OF PERMITS TO CONSTRUCT</B>
<P>
A permit to construct shall expire one year from the
date of issuance unless an extension of time has been approved
in writing by the Executive Officer.
</BODY>

</HTML>
