<HEAD>
<TITLE>RULE 209. Transfer and Voiding of Permits</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted January 9, 1976)(Amended November 1, 1985)<BR>
(Amended January 5, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 209. TRANSFER AND VOIDING OF PERMITS</B>
<P>
 A permit shall not be transferable, whether by operation of law
or otherwise, either from one location to another, from one piece
of equipment to another, or from one person to another.
<P>
 When equipment which has been granted a permit is altered, changes
location, or no longer will be operated by the permittee, the
permit shall become void.  For the purposes of this rule, mergers,
name changes, or incorporations by an individual owner or partnership
composed of individuals shall not constitute a transfer.
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

</DOC>
