<HEAD>
<TITLE>RULE 215. Permits Deemed Denied</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
 (Adopted January 1, 1976)(Amended January 5, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 215. PERMITS DEEMED DENIED</B>
<P>
 The applicant may deem an application for a permit to construct
denied, and appeal such denial to the District Hearing Board pursuant
to Rule 216, if the Executive Officer has failed to either approve
or deny the application for a permit to construct within
the time period specified by Rule 210(d).
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

</DOC>
