<HTML>

<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="sean wu">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Nate Natzke">
</HEAD>

<TITLE>RULE 301.1 - Permit Fee Rates (Rescinded June 1, 1990)</TITLE>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted October 15, 1982)(Rescinded June 3, 1983)<BR>
(Adopted June 3, 1983)(Amended May 4, 1984)(Amended July 6, 1984)
<BR>
(Amended May 1, 1987)(Amended June 5, 1987)(Amended June 3, 1988)
<BR>
(Amended June 2, 1989)(Amended January 5, 1990)(Rescinded June 1, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 301.1. PERMIT FEE RATES</B>
<P>
Refer to Rule 301 which was amended by the District Board on June 1, 1990 for permit fee rates.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<B>DO NOT USE FROM HERE ON.  FOR INFORMATION PURPOSES ONLY.</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
(Adopted October 15, 1982)(Rescinded June 3, 1983)<BR>
(Adopted June 3, 1983)(Amended May 4, 1984)(Amended July 6, 1984)
<BR>
(Amended May 1, 1987)(Amended June 5, 1987)(Amended June 3, 1988)
<BR>
(Amended June 2, 1989)(Amended January 5, 1990)
<P>
<B>RULE 301.1 PERMIT FEE RATES</B>
<P>
(a) Application Filing Fee
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Except as otherwise provided in this paragraph, the application
filing fee required by subparagraph (c)(1) of Rule 301 shall be
$250.
<P>
<LI>In the case of small businesses, the application filing fee
shall be $160.
<P>
<LI>In the case of gasoline fueling equipment, the application
filing fee shall be $75.
<P>
<LI>In the case of equipment exempt prior to June 3, 1988, the
application filing fee shall be $100.  If during the period June
3, 1989, and the effective date of the rule, a higher application
filing fee was submitted the excess will be returned.
<P>
<LI>Change of Ownership
<P>
(A) When an application for change of ownership of a valid permit
to operate is filed within one (1) year from the last annual renewal
of the permit to operate and there has been no change in the operation
of the affected equipment, the following requirements shall apply
to all businesses, except small businesses:
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
   (i) Applicant shall pay a filing fee of $110 for each permit
unit, except for gasoline fueling equipment; and
<P>
   (ii) Applicant shall pay a filing fee of $75 for gasoline fueling
equipment.
<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
(B) In the case of a change of ownership as described in subparagraph
(a)(4) of this Rule, when the application is filed for a small
business, the following requirements shall apply:
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
   (i) Applicant shall pay a filing fee of $110 for each permit
unit, except for gasoline fueling equipment; and
<P>
   (ii) Applicant shall pay a filing fee of $75 for gasoline fueling
equipment.
<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
(C) When an application for change of ownership of a Certificate
of Title For Emission Reduction Credit is filed and such certificate
has previously been issued and remains valid, the same requirements
shall apply as prescribed in subparagraphs (a)(4)(A) and (a)(4)(B)
of this Rule.
<P>
(D) The filing fees prescribed in subparagraph (a)(4), to be paid
for change of ownership of a permit, are equal to or lower than
the filing fees to be paid for a new permit.  If an application
for change of ownership of a permit is not filed within one (1)
year from the last annual renewal of the permit under the previous
owner, the fees prescribed in subparagraph (a)(4) shall not apply.
 Instead, an application for a new permit shall be submitted along
with the appropriate filing fee specified in subparagraph (a)(1),
(a)(2), or (a)(3).
<P>
</OL>
(b) Fees for Evaluation of Applications
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Permit Evaluation Fee
<P>
(A) Except as otherwise provided in this paragraph, the permit
evaluation fee required by subparagraph (d)(1) of Rule 301 shall
be determined in accordance with the schedules set forth in Rule
301.2.
<P>
(B) For applications submitted after July 1, 1984 for permits
to construct the categories of equipment listed in subparagraph
(a)(9) of Rule 301.2, the permit evaluation fee shall be an amount
equal to the total  actual and reasonable time incurred by the
District for evaluation of a permit to construct and/or permit
to operate, assessed at the rate of $75 per person per hour or
prorated portion thereof, and shall be paid by the applicant at
the time the permit to construct and/or permit to operate is granted
or denied.
<P>
 Payment shall be within the time period and upon the notification
specified in subparagraph (d)(1)(B) of Rule 301.
<P>
(C) Change of Ownership
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
   (i) When an application for change of ownership is filed and
comes within the provisions of subparagraph (a)(4) of this Rule,
except for small businesses and except for categories of equipment
listed in subparagraph (a)(9) of Rule 301.2, the permit evaluation
fee shall be one-half the amount set forth in subparagraph (b)(1)(A)
of this Rule.
<P>
   (ii) When an application for change of ownership is filed by
a small business and comes within the provisions of subparagraph
(a)(4)(B) of this Rule, no permit evaluation fee shall be paid.
<P>
   (iii) For categories of equipment listed in subparagraph (a)(9)
of Rule 301.2, the permit evaluation fee shall be the amount prescribed
in (b)(1)(B) of this Rule.
<P>
   (iv) When an application for change of ownership is filed by
operators of gasoline fueling equipment and comes within the provisions
of subparagraph (a)(4)(A) of this Rule, no permit evaluation fee
shall be paid.
<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
(D) When an application is filed for a permit involving alterations
or additions resulting in a change to any existing equipment for
which a permit to operate was granted and has not expired in accordance
with these Rules, or for a revision of conditions on a permit
to operate, except for categories of equipment listed in subparagraph
(a)(9) of Rule 301.2, the permit evaluation fees shall be one-half
the amount set forth in subparagraph (b)(1)(A) of this Rule. 
For categories of equipment listed in subparagraph (a)(9) of Rule
301.2, the permit evaluation fee shall be the amount prescribed
in subparagraph (b)(1)(B) of this Rule.
<P>
(E) Higher Fee for Failing to Obtain a Permit to Construct
<P>
When equipment is built, erected, installed, altered, or replaced
(except for identical replacement) without the owner/operator
obtaining a required permit to construct in accordance with Rule
201, the permit evaluation fee shall be 150 percent of the amount
set forth in subparagraphs (b)(1)(A), (B), or (D) of this rule.
 The assessment of such fee shall not limit the District's right
to pursue any other remedy provided for by law.  The provisions
of this paragraph shall not apply if a permit is required solely
due to a change in Rule 219 or for a change of ownership.  This
subparagraph shall not take effect until April 1, 1985 for those
applicants who file prior to receiving written notice from the
District.
<P>
<LI>Fee for Evaluation of Applications for Emission Reductions
<P>
When an application for effecting emission reductions, banking
emissions, obtaining a Certificate of Title For Emission Reduction
Credit, or registering such certificates is submitted, the evaluation
fee will be determined in the same manner as it would were the
equipment being evaluated for permit to construct and/or operate.
 If the application is for equipment or processes that do not
come under the provisions of the permit system, the evaluation
fee shall be assessed at the rate of $75 per person per hour or
prorated portion thereof.
<P>
</OL>
(c) Annual Operating Permit Fee
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Except as otherwise provided in this paragraph, the annual
operating permit fee required to be paid pursuant to paragraph
(e) of Rule 301 shall be determined in accordance with the schedules
set forth in Rule 301.2.
<P>
<LI>Credit for Solar Energy Equipment
<P>
Any permittee required to pay an annual operating permit fee shall
receive an annual fee credit for any solar energy equipment installed
at the site where the equipment under permit is located.
<P>
(A) Computation
<P>
The design capacity of the solar energy equipment expressed in
thousands of British Thermal Units (Btu) per hour shall be used
to determine the fee credit in accordance with Schedule 2 of Rule
301.2.
<P>
(B) Limitation
<P>
The solar energy credit shall not exceed the annual operating
permit renewal fee for all permits at the site where the solar
energy equipment is located.
<P>
</OL>
(d) Annual Permit Fee Based on Emissions
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Each source emitting in excess of 5 tons per year (rounded
to the nearest ton) of any one of the following air contaminants:
 gaseous sulfur compounds (expressed as sulfur dioxide), total
organic gases (other than those specified), specified organic
gases (listed in paragraph (b) of Rule 301.2), oxides of nitrogen
(expressed as nitrogen dioxide), or particulate matter, and in
excess of 100 tons per year (rounded to the nearest ton) for carbon
monoxide, shall be assessed a fee for every ton in excess of the
first 5 tons of that contaminant as prescribed in paragraph (b)
of Rule 301.2.
<P>
<LI>Each source emitting a toxic air contaminant as listed in
subparagraph (b)(2) and (b)(3) of Rule 301.2 shall be assessed
an additional fee as prescribed in subparagraph (b)(2) and (b)(3)
of Rule 301.2.
<P>
</OL>
(e) A fee of $13 shall be charged for a duplicate or reissued
permit.
<P>
(f) Reinstatement Fee
<P>
The reinstatement fee shall be 50 percent of the amount of fees
due at the time the application or permit expired, the appropriate
application filing fee, or $100 per application or permit, whichever
is lower.  Payment of all overdue fees and the reinstatement fee
shall accompany the request for reinstatement.
<P>
(g) Environmental Impact Analysis, Air Quality Analysis, and Notification
of Significant Projects
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Environmental Impact Analysis
<P>
When an Environmental Impact Report or Negative Declaration as
described in subparagraph (j)(1) of Rule 301 must be prepared,
the fee shall be assessed at the rate of $75 per person per hour
or prorate portion thereof.
<P>
<LI>Air Quality Analysis
<P>
When air quality simulation modeling as described in subparagraph
(j)(2) of Rule 301 must be performed or verified, the fee shall
be assessed at the rate of $75 per person per hour or prorated
portion thereof.
<P>
<LI>Public Notification of Significant Projects
<P>
Pursuant to Rule 212(e), the District staff may prepare the public
notice to be distributed by the permit-to-construct applicant.
 The cost of preparation of this notice shall be assessed to the
applicant at the rate of $25 per person per hour or prorated portion
thereof.
</OL>
<P>
<HR>
<P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
<P>

