<HEAD>

<TITLE>RULE 408 - Circumvention</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="sean wu">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="sean wu">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted May 7, 1976)
<P>
<B>RULE 408. CIRCUMVENTION</B> 
<P>
 A person shall not build, erect, install, or use any equipment,
the use of which, without resulting in a reduction in the total
release of air contaminants to the atmosphere, reduces or conceals
an emission which would otherwise constitute a violation of Chapter
3 (commencing with Section 41700) of Part 4, of Division 26 of
the Health and Safety Code or of these rules.  This rule shall
not apply to cases in which the only violation involved is of
Section 48700 of the Health and Safety Code, or Rule 402 of these
Rules.
<P>
 
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

</DOC>
