<HEAD>

<TITLE>RULE 432 - Gasoline Specifications</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted May 7, 1976)
<P>
<B>RULE 432. GASOLINE SPECIFICATIONS</B>
<P>
 A person shall not sell or supply for use within the District
as a fuel for motor vehicles defined by the Vehicle Code of the
State of California, gasoline having a degree of unsaturation
greater than that indicated by a Bromine Number of 30 as determined
by ASTM Method D1159-66.
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

