<HEAD>

<TITLE>RULE 470 - Asphalt Air Blowing</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Ernest Pang">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

(Adopted May 7, 1976)
<P>
<B>RULE 470. ASPHALT AIR BLOWING</B>
<P>
 A person shall not operate or use any equipment for the air blowing
of asphalt unless all gases, vapors and gas-entrained effluents
from such equipment are:
<P>
(a) Incinerated at temperatures of not less than 760oC (1400oF)
for a period of not less than 0.3 second, or
<P>
(b) Processed in such a manner determined by the Air Pollution
Control Officer to be equally, or more, effective for the purpose
of air pollution control than subsection (a).
</BODY>

</HTML>
<P>

