<TITLE>RULE 1102.1 - Perchloroethylene Dry Cleaning Systems</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted June 6, 1980)(Amended February 13, 1981)(Amended April
2, 1982)
<BR>
(Amended April 3, 1987)(Amended December 7, 1990)(Repealed December
9, 1994)
<P>
<B>RULE 1102.1. PERCHLOROETHYLENE DRY CLEANING SYSTEMS</B>
<P>
Repealed by the South Coast Air Quality Management District Board
on December 9, 1994 in accordance with the adoption of Rule 1421
- Control of Perchloroethylene Emissions from Dry Cleaning Operations.
</BODY>

